---
// Capabilities.astro — Core primitives grid
---

<section id="primitives" class="section-padding px-6">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="reveal mb-16 md:mb-20">
      <p class="text-signal text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-4">
        Core Primitives
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-gradient text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-display font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">
        The layer beneath trust
      </h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        The hardest systems depend on authority, evidence, time, and coordination under pressure. I work where those things stop being assumptions and become structure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Primitives Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">

      <!-- 1. Authority Models — primary weight -->
      <div class="reveal glass-card p-7 md:p-8 group hover:border-signal/20 transition-all duration-500" style="transition-delay: 0ms;">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-signal-faint flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:bg-signal/15 transition">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-signal" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z M2 17l10 5 10-5 M2 12l10 5 10-5" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-semibold text-lg mb-2 tracking-tight">Authority Models</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Who can act, under what rules, with what proof, and how that changes over time.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 2. Verifiable Workflows -->
      <div class="reveal glass-card p-7 md:p-8 group hover:border-signal/20 transition-all duration-500" style="transition-delay: 80ms;">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-signal-faint flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:bg-signal/15 transition">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-signal" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M3 12h4l3-9 4 18 3-9h4" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-semibold text-lg mb-2 tracking-tight">Verifiable Workflows</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Steps, decisions, and evidence that can be modelled, enforced, and replayed.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 3. Provenance -->
      <div class="reveal glass-card p-7 md:p-8 group hover:border-signal/20 transition-all duration-500" style="transition-delay: 160ms;">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-signal-faint flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:bg-signal/15 transition">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-signal" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M9 5H2v14h20V5h-7 M9 5a3 3 0 106 0 M9 5h6" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-semibold text-lg mb-2 tracking-tight">Provenance</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Origin, chain of action, and accountability made visible across actors and time.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 4. Incentive Design -->
      <div class="reveal glass-card p-7 md:p-8 group hover:border-signal/20 transition-all duration-500" style="transition-delay: 240ms;">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-signal-faint flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:bg-signal/15 transition">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-signal" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M12 8c-2.21 0-4 1.79-4 4s1.79 4 4 4 4-1.79 4-4-1.79-4-4-4z M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-semibold text-lg mb-2 tracking-tight">Incentive Design</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Demand sinks, supply pressure, reward flows, and flywheels that survive real behaviour.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 5. System Primitives -->
      <div class="reveal glass-card p-7 md:p-8 group hover:border-signal/20 transition-all duration-500" style="transition-delay: 320ms;">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-signal-faint flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:bg-signal/15 transition">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-signal" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M4 4h7v7H4z M13 4h7v7h-7z M4 13h7v7H4z M13 13h7v7h-7z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-semibold text-lg mb-2 tracking-tight">System Primitives</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">The foundational models, boundaries, and execution paths that products and platforms rely on.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 6. Protocol Structures -->
      <div class="reveal glass-card p-7 md:p-8 group hover:border-signal/20 transition-all duration-500" style="transition-delay: 400ms;">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-signal-faint flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:bg-signal/15 transition">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-signal" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2z M11 19.93c-3.95-.49-7-3.85-7-7.93 0-.62.08-1.21.21-1.79L9 15v1c0 1.1.9 2 2 2v1.93z M18.9 17.39c-.26-.81-1-1.39-1.9-1.39h-1v-3c0-.55-.45-1-1-1H8v-2h2c.55 0 1-.45 1-1V7h2c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2v-.41c2.93 1.19 5 4.06 5 7.41 0 2.08-.8 3.97-2.1 5.39z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-semibold text-lg mb-2 tracking-tight">Protocol Structures</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Reusable coordination and economic systems designed to compound beyond one-off applications.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
